title: Bug 6322 - All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: Bug 6322 - All types dialog shows obfuscated classes. JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd') which are showing up prominently in the Open Type dialog.
OB: The Open Type dialog is displaying obfuscated classes from JDK 1.4, including classes with names like 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', and 'd'.
SR:
To reproduce:
1. Launch the software
2. Open the Open Type dialog
3. Observe the displayed obfuscated class names from JDK 1.4
